:QUOTE
The best travel work setup is the one you actually carry with you.

:INFO
Travel-Proof Remote Work Station
A portable work setup must handle variable environments: cafe tables, coworking desks, hotel rooms, and outdoor terraces. Prioritize weight, redundancy, and connectivity over raw performance.

:COUNTER.half
5 kg
Target total bag weight including laptop
|
:COUNTER.half
2 Screens
Minimum for productive knowledge work

:PATH
Choose Your Hardware
Laptop with long battery life first. Add a portable monitor only if your work requires it. A compact keyboard and mouse reduce strain on long work days.

:PATH
Solve Connectivity
Carry a primary SIM and a backup eSIM plan. A portable travel router lets you share hotel ethernet or create a private WiFi network from any source.

:PATH
Handle Power Anywhere
A 65W or higher GaN charger handles laptop and peripherals from one plug. Carry the right adapter kit for your target regions. A small power bank covers cafe sessions.

:CHECKLIST
Packing Checklist
[ ] Laptop with charger and cable
[ ] Portable monitor with USB-C connection
[ ] Compact wireless keyboard and mouse
[ ] Travel router and ethernet adapter
[ ] GaN multi-port charger
[ ] Universal travel adapter
[ ] Noise-cancelling headphones
[ ] Local SIM or eSIM plan activated

:NOTE
Test your full setup at home before a long trip. Discovering a missing cable or a broken port at a destination costs more than the cable itself.
